enemies - package enemies
 
Enemy - Class in enemies
Enemy is the overarching abstract class that defines the behavior of enemies in the game.
Enemy(double, double) - Constructor for class enemies.Enemy
Creates and enemy with initial x,y and a default health level
EnemyTests - Class in tests
Tests all subclasses of Enemy, and therefore tests the abstract class Enemy itself
EnemyTests() - Constructor for class tests.EnemyTests
 
EstuaryAdventureMain - Class in main
This main control structure of this game is very similar to an online tutorial series entitled "Java Game Development" This is because Abraham made a game a couple of years ago using these tutorials for fun, and so our implementation ended up being very similar.
EstuaryAdventureMain() - Constructor for class main.EstuaryAdventureMain
creates the Main Game by calling init()
EstuaryView - Class in mainView
Handles rendering the View for all games
EstuaryView() - Constructor for class mainView.EstuaryView
 
executeAnimationSequence() - Method in class animation.AnimationCrabPIckUpTrash
executes the animation sequence
